reviews.text: The best part of the visit was the reptile exhibit where I got to see a dragon and the colorful and poisonous frogs from the Amazon. Their bright yellow and bluish/purplish colors were so beautiful. We also had a fun time feeding the giraffe and petting the goats. The place was clean and the personnel were friendly and helpful. The walk around the park was very pleasant and enjoyable. The weather was temperate that added more to trees that abundantly inhabited the place.

While the entrance is not fancy you quickly find out it drops you directly into the action. I beautiful walk through tropical bird environment that thrills children and adults alike. Moving on to the elephants you are sill thinking this is a standard zoo adventure until you come out on the Savanna. 40 acres of beautiful environment designed so well you don't notice the barriers between the hunters and the prey. Off in the distance a herd of elephants sways while different antelope types wander and occasionally bound through. A pride of lions sits to one side. Lounging on rocks and lording it over all, cubs playing and lionesses watching over them. A rhinoceros wanders through with her baby at her side. Amazing everyone. Next is on to the giant enclosed tropical rain forest complete with waterfall and fowl of all types. The zoo in Fresno is well worth the visit. If you in town at loose ends or looking for something on the weekend to do with yourself or the family. You can't lose with this one.

So much fun! I hadn't been to this zoo in 10 years and so much has changed.  They have done some amazing improvements and additions. It is very affordable and a great time for all ages.  The exhibits are all well done and you can easily view the animals.  There are also two great locations to eat delicious food at affordable prices.

Families favorite zoo! Highly recommended to anyone who enjoys wildlife. They are undergoing some construction for more exhibits, but there is still plenty to do and see! Our favorite exhibit is the stingray pool! Pet huge rays and sharks! Can't wait to see what is in store for the new exhibits!

Incredible zoo for Fresno. Check out the bird show - we were totally surprised and impressed! Owls, talking parrots, giant cranes, cockatoos, and some other surprises. 

Lots of other fun animals to see and an impressive reptile house. My kids are happy and worn out every time we visit without fail.
Truly a hand crafted winery.  Family own since the 20's. we had a super fun time with the owner. They are a piece of Fresno history.

Nonini winery has been a favorite of mine for many years. The wines they have here are some of my favorite in all of Fresno / Madera area. Part of the draw is the staff which iokay s always fun to talk to. They are great for pouring a taste, talking shop and cracking jokes. Also the warehouse is fun to go in and hang out in.
Nonini Winery has been family owned for 4 generations. The owners were there and spent considerable time chatting with us and showing us around.  We loved the history and stories.
Family owned vineyard since 1935- wonderful to talk with the nonini family and taste grandfathers legacy! Very reasonable priced wines- a MUST if you're in Fresno!!
Really fun and lay back but only one restroom
GREAT UNIVERSITY!! The vibe is amazing and fun a good university for both upcoming freshman and transfers
They host some pretty cool events like Queer Prom

While the school is decent itself there are other issues that can pose problems for others.  The parking is absolutely terrible.  Expect 15+ minutes searching and then another 10+ walking.  The campus is huge with no way of getting around quickly so if you have back to back classes you spend your 15 minute break walking to class so you can't eat, study, write down remaining notes from last class.  If your professor goes over time you are left rushing.  Most professors choose not to work with you or help.  If you can't do it when they want you to then you are out of luck.  Most professors favor ones who are doing good already and don't want to help struggling students who are asking for the help.  If you have a disability a vast majority of the professors make you feel bad about it and a pain to work with.  Some will go out of their way to help you as much as they can.  Tuition here is absurdly high for no reason.  Community college will cost you ~$600 per semester while going here will cost you $3,200.  They get a grant to help students get tablets for their classes and instead of letting the students spend it they spend it themselves on loaners which cripple students who find it useful for their other classes and can't afford one do to high school cost already and don't want to go further in debt with loans.  They would rather build new buildings than alleviate student parking problems.

This used to be a school I respected ever since I was a kid. Now that my wife attends here it has become apparent to me that this school is by far not what it seems. Professors spend most of class time ranting about personal issues instead of teaching. The class availability is ridiculous sometimes there is only one or two classes available and even then one will usually close or drop off leaving students puzzled with nothing but an o well giving from administration. If someone was to spend 6k a semester at my business I would make sure they were taking care of. In my opinion this school has lost its shine now its just another over priced collage full of excuses.
Went to a meeting in the Sid Craig School of Business building. First time in this building. WOW! Very nice meeting room! Very impressed!
Very nice ambience With Good crowd. And there service is best. Very good looking and well dressed Staff. And no doubt the Food is very good.

Very delicious food! For an  appetizer we had the bruschetta. Very generous slice of cheese and toppings on it with a little bit of spice. I had the salmon that was the best that I have ever had. Sweet crunch on the edge of the seared salmon that was cooked just right, not overcooked and dried but very moist. The dessert was yummy too. Overall a very delicious dinner with very nice and attentive waiters.
Sunday brunch has great tasting food and delicious desserts.  The atmosphere is cozy.  Reservations are recommended, there is always a line out the door.
Had a company lunch of 50. The patio space was perfect. They blocked off an area  for us. The 3 choices were: 1) salmon with Salad. 2) tenderloin, and chicken
The staff was superb and the buffet was tasty. Very nice place. Super clean and very pretty. A bit upper scale for some people but still super cool.

This is going to sound strange, since I gave it only three stars, but the food is incredible. There's some kind of flavor they put in everything that I have a hard time describing, but it's delicious. The reason for knocking off two stars is because it's always dirty inside, the tables are greasy and it's humid and hot inside even if it's cool outside. The floor was weirdly greasy one time, I almost slipped half a dozen times. Really, though, I would absolutely recommend this place if you can push past the sticky greasy tables.

Dusty Buns has very delicious tasting food with good quality and fresh, local flavors. I really recommend that you try this place at least once. And if you can't stop by their restaurant, you can always stop by their food truck! (the schedule is on their website)
We really loved this place. Unique food and amazing vegetarian options. Staff were very relaxed and knowledgeable of the menu. Try this place for a fresh change of pace

Brian(below) i appreciate your review for your honesty, however, you're crazy. 
Dusty Buns has been creating amazingly delicious menus since day one. Their fries are perfectly seasoned half fingerling potatoes with a spicy garlic sauce made fresh in house. The salads are simple and balanced. The sandwiches are all uniquely concocted to spotlight local Ag and suppliers. The Dusty bun itself is a classic along with other great specials such as the Lamb burger and the grilled cheese with brie. The sandwiches are the perfect size to pair with a salad, fries or soups which are warm, patiently simmered and full of flavor. and the tangerine dipped in chocolate ganache is perfect for dessert.  I would and do often recommend this local necessity. not only raising the bar for local cuisine, but thriving on the supply and demand of our local community. Thanks Dusty Buns!
Lovely sandwich shop! Friendly service, food tasted great. I recommend recommend to anyone who wants a simple, fresh sandwich or burger.
Real Italian Family Restaurant

Their vegetarian burger, with the patty made in-house, is almost flavorless. They charge around $9 just for that, and it doesn't even  come with cheese to help make up for the lack of flavor. So I had to add fries and cheese in order to make it edible. Overall, I was not satisfied paying over $15 for something that I could order at another local restaurant for about $10 or $11 and with more flavor. If you come here, you may want to skip out on the vegetarian burger, or bring your own seasoning!

The food itself was pretty tasty but certainly not worth the price! The main issue was our server, she took our daughters drink to another table then went and took it away and brought it to us and she left our food in the window for 10 minutes! The only reason I didn’t complain was because it gave the food time to cool for our daughter. Won’t be coming here again I can get a better burger, better service and for a cheaper price at Doghouse.

You are slipping, Irene's.  Saturday, April 6th our party of 5 had dinner outdoors.  Beautiful weather!  Waitress brought drinks and told us the Raspberry Iced Tea was refillable.  No refills were offered, nor did the waitress come by much to check on our party of 5 (two couples and a spare lady).  My sister has had stomach staple surgery so she and I often share a meal-- they usually charge a small fee for an extra plate which is fine with us.  Last night, when it was time to bring out the salad (and extra plate) the waitress brought 2 salads so we had to ask for the extra plate-- and that had to be explained to the waitress all over again since our initial order taking.  The remainder of the order took a longer time than usual for food to arrive from the kitchen.  My husband ordered a burger with onion rings and he received french fries on his plate.  During our meal, we had a street person come by and ask (over the fence) if he could shine our shoes in exchange for cash.  Finally our food arrives, and we got the extra plate...  when the ticket arrives, we were charged for an extra side salad and the extra plate fee.  And no refills offered during our meal.  Oh, the food is tasty and healthy.  But, your service and understanding of your customer's needs and wants leaves much to be desired, compared to our previous visits within the past 6 months.  Too bad, Irene's; I hope this does not 'catch up with you' and cause a decrease in business...
First time herre.. Service was great n so was the f😀😀d. (Shout out to the chef) Outside seating very nice n comfy. I recommend this place. Coming back again soon.
American food and the feeling here is better than most. i've had nothing but pleasant experiences here and plan to keep coming back. it has an awesome atmosphere.

Love this place.. Have never been disappointed. The Sweet Potato Fries are a MUST HAVE to start the meal off. There a staple. Food is cooked perfectly. The wait staff is friendly and energetic. Great place to take friends and family to.

I googled "Sweet Potato Fries near me" and I was led here! What a gem! Great service. This is a very nice bistro with high quality food & specials. The art and decor is beautiful.  A high end menu with  personable service.  They care about their patrons. And yes...the sweet potato fries w/ jalapeno aioli sauce was amazing!!!

Our first time,we fell in love. The waitresses were awesome so friendly an through. We'll definitely be back, the food was excellent, i had sea bass over risotto with veggies amazing. My wife had short Ribs, she loved it. Thx

The first visit to Max's was with a group of colleagues for a Christmas dinner. The decor of the restaurant is very warm and welcoming with reds and dark brown colors. While the space is quite large, it is split into smaller areas and allows decent privacy. I would call it a good place for a date or a business dinner.

Food was good, although my salmon was not fully cooked - another minute on the stove would not be bad. Chocolate molten cake with vanilla ice cream, whipped cream and a few berries was my favorite - rich in flavor, moderately sweet, a little crisp on the outside and deliciously liquid on the inside. 

Service was outstanding. Our waitress was down to earth and friendly, something that is often rare in fancy restaurants where they feel they have to be stuck up to create an appropriate atmosphere. 

Overall, I think I would come back. It is not very friendly to a vegan or vegetarian, but their sweet potato fried are to die for, not literally...
Our server Benson did not lie to us about the quality of food. +++ Rating. They host private events as well as catering. They offer a good selection of wine and beer and a full bar to boot.
If you want a nice romantic place with lots of luxury this is the place to go.

Eaten here multiple times, they’re a growing local business and deserve all the customer support they can get. They have the best, and freshest authentic Mexican food I’ve ever eaten in Fresno and their staff are very fast and polite. Would highly recommend the Super Nachos and Super Burritos ☺️❤️😋

First and foremost, I'd like to state that the food here is phenomenal, let's just get that out of the way. If it was ranked strictly on the food, I'd give 20 stars however, anyone who frequents here knows that if you come at lunch that u better expect a line out the door and unless you sent someone super early to hold a table for you then you better get your food to go cause it's standing room only at that point. The other thing I had a problem with is it seems like every time I've gone the smell of bleach\cleaner is quite pungent, to the point where it affects my appetite which isn't good. All in all, I'd still highly recommend this place, it never disappoints!
A preferred spot for quality Mexican food. Came here on a Friday I think. I look forward to a return trip. I can see why they have so many good reviews.

Good location for tasty mexican food. I wanted to post a food pic but it looked so good I couldn't stop. I had a brother come into town and asked me to take him back here. Menu is like a cafe in Indianapolis I liked.
Can't get enough... gotta have my weekly burrito fix... the asada is bomb!! & the salsas are Awesome!! 🍽😁 don't change a thing keep doing what your doing... I'm gonna have to try the menudo next.
Quiet place, very friendly staff and a broad enough menu to keep everyone guessing what they want. Lunch specials are around $10 with most entrees around $14. Great place for a quick bite.

Everyone here was so extremly nice to me and they all were stop helpful! (I've never eaten Thai before) The food was great, the drink was great & the service was just awesome! I wish all places were as friendly as they were here!

Came in today. Waited 45 mins thinking the food is almost ready. When I go and ask the worker about the wait time for food, she says it will take another 10 mins. Canceled the order and left with no food. Who takes 50+ mins to cook during lunch hour. Plus it was only one person serving all the customers and it took some time before she came to take our order. If you know it's going to be busy, have more people to help during peak hours. This is unacceptable. I would not give a star but that's the only option available. I would not recommend this place.

You couldn't ask for a better Panda the green beans and chicken was better than I've had anywhere it was super unlike the one that's over by the Vallarta store on Clinton and Weber this one here gets an A+ and that one over there gets an F don't bother to go there cuz their food is terrible. Also the help over here on Shaw is much more friendly and it's an all-around better experience
Place is decorated really nice for the holidays and food/service is good. Karaoke in the summer....
